By Week 35, the pattern of the term had come into sharp relief. Power was no longer merely leaning against the guardrails; it was testing how far they would bend before they broke. Immigration raids, media intimidation, and the hollowing out of science and public health all moved in concert, not as isolated abuses but as parts of a single governing style. The week\'92s events showed a White House that treated law as a tool, not a limit, and treated truth and expertise as obstacles to be managed. What had once been extraordinary\'97federal troops in cities, emergency rhetoric over routine policy disputes, the president threatening broadcasters\'97was on its way to becoming ordinary. That normalization, more than any single order or lawsuit, defined the week. It set the tone.\
